# Vistral Lab - Design System Rules

## Prophero Design System

**Reference:** [Prophero React Design System](https://vistral-design-system.vercel.app/?path=/docs/introduction--docs) — check variants, props, examples, accessibility.

## Design Tokens

**Location:** `src/app/vistral.css` or `prophero.css` in this project. **Variables:** prefix `--prophero-*` (colors, spacing, radius, typography). Use CSS variables for dynamic values; Tailwind when possible; constants from `@/lib/constants` for breakpoints/spacing.

## Grid Responsivo

Breakpoints in `@/lib/constants` and CSS: XS–XXL with margins/gutters. Classes: `container-margin`, `gutter`. Import BREAKPOINTS, SPACING from `@/lib/constants`.

## Theme

`src/app/globals.css` imports Tailwind and design tokens. Dark mode via `.dark` class if applicable.

## Component Patterns

**Always use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils`** to combine classes (clsx + tailwind-merge). Never concatenate class strings by hand.

**Variants:** Use CVA (class-variance-authority) with `variant` and `size`; export `componentVariants` and use `cn(componentVariants({ variant, size, className }))`.

**Refs:** Components wrapping native elements MUST use `forwardRef` and pass `ref` to the DOM element.

**Accessibility:** Use Radix UI for keyboard, focus, ARIA; don't reinvent modals, selects, dropdowns.
